    "long_instructions": "## Webpage Responsiveness\r\n\r\n###Step 1: Test for responsiveness\r\n- Resize the browser window to simulate a smaller screen or tablet.\r\n- Then toggle between **Desktop** and **Mobile** on the top right.\r\n- Log issues using the Responsiveness Checklist.\r\n\r\n###Step 2: Debug\r\n- Pick 1–2 logged issues.\r\n- Use AI to fix these issues.\r\n- Save the updated version, e.g. **V3 - fixed cards layout for mobile**\r\n\r\n###Step 3: Iterate\r\n- Continue to work on at least two pages making them responsive to different screen sizes.\r\n\r\n:::details [Not sure how to prompt AI?]\r\nTry modifying these examples:\r\n- *“Make the navigation collapse into a hamburger menu on small screens.”*\r\n- *“Stack the sidebar below main content when screen width < 768px.”*\r\n:::",
